üü¶ VOUCH ‚Äî FINAL SYSTEM FLOW & FEATURE SPEC
Decentralized Escrow for Social Commerce (Lisk Network)
0Ô∏è‚É£ ONE-LINE POSITIONING (WAJIB DIPAKAI DI ATAS)
Vouch is a decentralized escrow infrastructure that brings marketplace-level trust to Instagram, WhatsApp, and TikTok commerce ‚Äî without a marketplace.
1Ô∏è‚É£ CORE PROBLEM (FINAL VERSION)
Social commerce in Southeast Asia happens inside private chats (DMs), but there is no neutral trust layer.
Buyers are afraid to pay first
Sellers are afraid to ship first
Platforms like Instagram & WhatsApp do not provide escrow
Existing solutions require centralized marketplaces or manual trust
Vouch solves the ‚Äútrust vacuum‚Äù in DM-based commerce by turning a simple payment link into a decentralized escrow contract.
2Ô∏è‚É£ DESIGN PHILOSOPHY (IMPORTANT FOR JURY)
Web2 UX, Web3 trust
No login / no registration
Wallet = identity
Smart contract = source of truth
Backend = replaceable coordinator (not custodian)
3Ô∏è‚É£ ACTORS IN THE SYSTEM
Actor	Role
Seller	Creates escrow link, ships goods
Buyer	Pays via crypto or fiat
Smart Contract (Lisk)	Holds escrow logic & funds
Backend (Coordinator)	Verifies fiat payment, relays tx
Xendit	Fiat payment confirmation oracle
4Ô∏è‚É£ HIGH-LEVEL FLOW (ICONIC FLOW)
Paste link in DM ‚Üí Buyer pays ‚Üí Seller ships ‚Üí Buyer confirms ‚Üí Funds released
This is the only flow you highlight publicly.
5Ô∏è‚É£ DETAILED END-TO-END FLOW
üß© STEP 1 ‚Äî Seller Creates Escrow Link (On-Chain)
Seller actions
Connects Lisk wallet
Inputs:
Item name & description
Price (USDC or IDR equivalent)
Escrow duration (e.g. 3 / 5 / 7 days)
Accepted payment methods:
USDC (on Lisk)
Fiat via QRIS / VA (Xendit)
On-chain
createEscrow() called on VouchEscrow.sol
Escrow created with:
seller address
amount
expiry timestamp
status = CREATED
Output
Unique Vouch Link (escrowId encoded)
Seller pastes link into Instagram / WhatsApp / TikTok DM
üß© STEP 2 ‚Äî Buyer Opens Link (No Login)
Buyer experience
Opens Vouch link
Sees:
Item details
Seller wallet (shortened)
Escrow timer
Payment options:
Pay with Crypto
Pay with QRIS / VA
No account. No signup.
üß© STEP 3A ‚Äî Buyer Pays with Crypto (Fully On-Chain)
Buyer actions
Connects wallet
Approves USDC
Calls fundEscrow()
On-chain
USDC transferred directly to escrow contract
Escrow status ‚Üí FUNDED
Funds are non-custodial & locked
üß© STEP 3B ‚Äî Buyer Pays with Fiat (Hybrid, Jury-Safe)
Buyer actions
Selects QRIS / VA
Pays via Xendit
Backend role
Receives Xendit callback
Verifies:
payment amount
escrowId metadata
payment status = PAID
On-chain
Backend calls markFiatFunded(escrowId)
Backend-funded hot wallet transfers USDC into escrow
Escrow status ‚Üí FUNDED
üìå Important framing
Xendit never controls escrow logic
Smart contract still decides release / refund
üß© STEP 4 ‚Äî Seller Ships Goods (Off-Chain)
Seller ships item
No blockchain interaction
Timer continues counting down
üß© STEP 5 ‚Äî Buyer Confirms Receipt
Buyer actions
Clicks ‚ÄúConfirm Item Received‚Äù
Calls releaseEscrow()
On-chain
Escrow status ‚Üí RELEASED
Funds transferred to seller wallet
üß© STEP 6 ‚Äî Auto-Release or Auto-Refund (Fail-Safes)
If buyer is inactive
Escrow auto-releases to seller after expiry
If seller cancels / timeout
Escrow auto-refunds buyer
All enforced on-chain.
6Ô∏è‚É£ SMART CONTRACT ARCHITECTURE (FINAL)
üß† VouchEscrow.sol
Core State
enum Status {
  CREATED,
  FUNDED,
  RELEASED,
  REFUNDED,
  DISPUTED
}
Key Functions
createEscrow()
fundEscrow() (crypto)
markFiatFunded() (backend oracle)
releaseEscrow()
refundEscrow()
autoSettle()
Guarantees
Backend cannot steal funds
Backend cannot override escrow rules
Funds only move via deterministic logic
7Ô∏è‚É£ BACKEND RESPONSIBILITIES (MINIMIZED)
Backend is not trusted custody.
Backend handles:
Xendit payment verification
Relaying fiat ‚Üí on-chain funding
Indexing escrow events
Providing escrow history API
Backend cannot:
Withdraw escrow funds
Release funds arbitrarily
Modify escrow rules
8Ô∏è‚É£ FINAL FEATURE LIST (CURATED, NOT BLOATED)
üîê Trust & Safety
On-chain escrow
Seller-defined timeout
Auto-release & auto-refund
Immutable escrow history
üí∏ Payments
USDC on Lisk
QRIS / VA / e-wallet via Xendit
Unified escrow regardless of payment type
üßæ Transparency
Public escrow status
Wallet-based identity
On-chain event tracking
üßë‚Äçüíª UX
No login / no register
Shareable payment link
Mobile-first design
Web2-friendly language
9Ô∏è‚É£ WHERE DECENTRALIZATION MATTERS (JURY SLIDE)
Layer	Centralized?	Why
Escrow logic	‚ùå No	Trust anchor
Funds custody	‚ùå No	User safety
Fiat confirmation	‚úÖ Yes	Fiat reality
Backend	‚ö†Ô∏è Replaceable	Coordinator only
If the backend disappears, escrow funds remain safe on-chain.
üîö FINAL VERDICT STATEMENT (CLOSING LINE)
Vouch doesn‚Äôt try to replace marketplaces.
It replaces the missing trust layer in social commerce.
